aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w32-fSoften=1,100,0-rp-e365\" data-srcset=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QXVcHrAZYDC0S6aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w480-rj-l80-nu-e365 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QXVcHrAZYDC0S6aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w640-rj-l80-nu-e365 640w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QXVcHrAZYDC0S6aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w780-rj-l80-nu-e365 780w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QXVcHrAZYDC0S6aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w960-rj-l80-nu-e365 960w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QXVcHrAZYDC0S6aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w1200-rj-l80-nu-e365 1200w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-QXVcHrAZYDC0S6aH4oSY0cyP5C1c2vICmNp2N4dRvHDed7g-BPCxc_mA671mYCEMdMPOwyhYbYIDTZ0G4-uJ-1TgyO1IIQNfVfx4_5by0KLwCFK=w1600-rj-l80-nu-e365 1600w\" data-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n<figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">|&nbsp;<em>Netflix</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Notably, this is the scene where Jang Deok Su is pulled to his death by the unlikely heroine, Han Mi Nyeo. Of course, while the stepping stones looked like they were dozens of feet above the ground on the show, in real life, the set-up was much safer. According to behind-the-scenes footage, the set was only around 1.5 meters (or 4.9 feet) high, which CGI used to create the death-defying look.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_1150246\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"lazyload-ph lazyload no-js-hide wp-image-1150246 size-f